        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 2:10AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>The combination of abnormally hot temperatures and dew points
temperatures will produce heat index values up to 110 degrees for
a few hours this afternoon. A few locations may briefly experience
heat index values a degree or two above 110 degrees.

If spending time outside today, drink plenty of water, wear light
weight and light colored clothing, and take frequent breaks from
the heat. Young children and pets should never be left unattended
in vehicles.
</description>
